Here's a comprehensive workshop plan for introducing Java to beginners:

# Java Programming Workshop for Beginners (2 Hours)

## Introduction (20 minutes)
- Welcome and workshop overview
- Java's role in modern software development
  - Enterprise applications
  - Android development
  - Web services and APIs
- Career opportunities in Java development
- Setting up development environment (pre-installed Eclipse/IntelliJ)

## Basic Concepts (25 minutes)
- Understanding Java syntax
```java
public class HelloWorld {
    public static void main(String[] args) {
        System.out.println("Hello, World!");
    }
}
```
- Data types and variables
- Basic operators
- Hands-on Exercise: Creating first Java program

## Control Flow Structures (30 minutes)
- if-else statements
- loops (for, while)
- Practice Exercise: Temperature converter program
```java
public class TemperatureConverter {
    public static void main(String[] args) {
        double fahrenheit = 75.0;
        double celsius = (fahrenheit - 32) * 5/9;
        System.out.println(fahrenheit + "°F = " + celsius + "°C");
    }
}
```

## Object-Oriented Basics (25 minutes)
- Classes and objects explained through real-world examples
- Simple class creation exercise
```java
public class Car {
    String model;
    int year;

    public void startEngine() {
        System.out.println("The " + year + " " + model + " is starting");
    }
}
```

## Interactive Coding Session (10 minutes)
- Common error debugging
- Best practices discussion
- IDE features demonstration

## Q&A and Assessment (10 minutes)
- Open discussion
- Quick quiz on key concepts
- Resources for continued learning:
  - Oracle Java Documentation
  - Online learning platforms
  - Java developer communities

